{
  "local_port": 39258,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What's a good moveset for Rockruff in Pokemon Sun and Moon?",
  "response": "Rockruff is a versatile Rock-type Pok\u00e9mon introduced in Generation VII, making its debut in **Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon**. With decent Attack and Speed stats, Rockruff can serve as an effective physical attacker or a support Pok\u00e9mon, especially when evolved into its various forms of **Lycanroc**. Below are some recommended movesets tailored for Rockruff in Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon, focusing on different roles it can fulfill in battles.\n\n---\n\n### **1. Physical Attacker Moveset**\n\n**Item:** **Choice Band** / **Life Orb**\n\n**Ability:** **Vital Spirit**  \n*Prevents Rockruff from falling asleep, ensuring consistent offensive pressure.*\n\n**EV Spread:**  \n- **252 Attack / 4 Defense / 252 Speed**  \n- **Nature:** **Jolly** (+Speed, -Special Attack) or **Adamant** (+Attack, -Special Attack)\n\n**Moves:**\n1. **Rock Slide**\n   - **Type:** Rock\n   - **Power:** 75\n   - **Accuracy:** 90%\n   - **Effect:** Standard Rock-type STAB move with a chance to flinch the opponent (30%). It also hits multiple targets in double battles.\n\n2. **Crunch**\n   - **Type:** Dark\n   - **Power:** 80\n   - **Accuracy:** 100%\n   - **Effect:** Provides coverage against Psychic and Ghost types, which are common weaknesses for Rock-type Pok\u00e9mon.\n\n3. **Earthquake** / **Stone Edge**\n   - **Earthquake**\n     - **Type:** Ground\n     - **Power:** 100\n     - **Accuracy:** 100%\n     - **Effect:** Broad coverage, especially effective against Steel, Fire, and Electric types.\n   - **Stone Edge**\n     - **Type:** Rock\n     - **Power:** 100\n     - **Accuracy:** 80%\n     - **Effect:** Higher critical-hit ratio compared to Rock Slide.\n\n4. **Swords Dance**\n   - **Type:** Normal\n   - **Effect:** Boosts Rockruff\u2019s Attack by two stages, significantly increasing its physical damage output.\n\n**Usage Tips:**\n- **Choice Band** locks Rockruff into the first move it uses, so choose the move that best fits your strategy.\n- **Life Orb** offers flexibility by allowing Rockruff to use different moves without being locked in, at the cost of some recoil damage.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Swords Dance Sweeper Moveset**\n\n**Item:** **Leftovers** / **Assault Vest**\n\n**Ability:** **Vital Spirit**  \n*Prevents sleep, ensuring uninterrupted setup.*\n\n**EV Spread:**  \n- **252 Attack / 4 Defense / 252 Speed**  \n- **Nature:** **Jolly** or **Adamant**\n\n**Moves:**\n1. **Swords Dance**\n   - **Type:** Normal\n   - **Effect:** Critical for boosting Rockruff\u2019s Attack stat, making subsequent physical moves much more potent.\n\n2. **Rock Slide**\n   - **Type:** Rock\n   - **Power:** 75\n   - **Accuracy:** 90%\n   - **Effect:** Reliable STAB move with flinch chance and multi-target capability.\n\n3. **Crunch**\n   - **Type:** Dark\n   - **Power:** 80\n   - **Accuracy:** 100%\n   - **Effect:** Covers weaknesses against Psychic and Ghost types.\n\n4. **Stealth Rock**\n   - **Type:** Rock\n   - **Effect:** Entry hazard that damages opponents as they switch in, providing passive damage and chip away at opposing teams.\n\n**Usage Tips:**\n- **Leftovers** provides consistent recovery, helping Rockruff stay in battles longer.\n- **Assault Vest** can be used if you prefer increased Special Defense at the cost of preventing status moves.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Support/Utility Moveset**\n\n**Item:** **Rocky Helmet** / **Focus Sash**\n\n**Ability:** **Vital Spirit**  \n*Prevents sleep, ensuring Rockruff can always perform its moves.*\n\n**EV Spread:**  \n- **252 HP / 172 Defense / 84 Speed**  \n- **Nature:** **Adamant** or **Careful**\n\n**Moves:**\n1. **Stealth Rock**\n   - **Type:** Rock\n   - **Effect:** Essential for setting up entry hazards that chip away at opposing teams.\n\n2. **Rock Slide**\n   - **Type:** Rock\n   - **Power:** 75\n   - **Accuracy:** 90%\n   - **Effect:** Provides STAB damage with flinch chance and can hit multiple foes.\n\n3. **Taunt** / **Thunder Wave**\n   - **Taunt**\n     - **Type:** Dark\n     - **Effect:** Prevents opponents from using status moves, forcing them to switch to offensive strategies.\n   - **Thunder Wave**\n     - **Type:** Electric\n     - **Effect:** Inflicts paralysis, reducing opponents' Speed and potentially causing them to be unable to move.\n\n4. **Crunch**\n   - **Type:** Dark\n   - **Power:** 80\n   - **Accuracy:** 100%\n   - **Effect:** Coverage against Psychic and Ghost types.\n\n**Usage Tips:**\n- **Rocky Helmet** causes damage to attackers that make contact, synergizing well with moves like Rock Slide.\n- **Focus Sash** ensures Rockruff can survive at least one hit, allowing it to set up or disrupt opponents early in the battle.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Evolution Consideration:** Evolving Rockruff into **Lycanroc (Midday Form)** can significantly enhance its stats and move pool. Lycanroc gains access to more powerful moves like Accelerock, making it an excellent choice for a faster and stronger Rock-type attacker.\n  \n- **Speed Handling:** Rockruff\u2019s Speed can be decent, but investing in Speed EVs and a **Jolly** nature can help outspeed key threats in the meta.\n\n- **Team Synergy:** Rockruff works well in teams that can cover its weaknesses, particularly against Water, Grass, Fighting, Ground, Steel, and Fairy types. Partners that can handle these threats will allow Rockruff to perform more effectively.\n\n---\n\nBy tailoring Rockruff\u2019s moveset to fit your battle strategy\u2014whether as a powerhouse attacker, a setup sweeper, or a supportive utility Pok\u00e9mon\u2014you can maximize its potential in **Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon**. Always consider the specific dynamics of your team and the common threats in your battle environment to choose the most effective moveset.",
